CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 1, 1941, pg. 22, reads: "The Rosette's Social Club, with headquarters at 605 Chauncey street, were snapped as they were completing plans for a unique social affair to be announced in near future. This group is not one of the newest in the city but extensive plans have been made for a year round program. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Nine women, members of "Rosette" Social Club, including woman seated on floor wearing dress with plaid skirt, collar, and sleeves, in Harris Studio with circular background
